AGENT AUDIT (unreviewed — treat claims as unverified)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

C++ header: include/emCore/emString.h
C++ implementation: src/emCore/emString.cpp

C++ public API:
  class emString:
  - emString() -- default constructor (empty string)
  - emString(const emString&) -- copy constructor (COW shallow copy via refcount)
  - emString(const char* p) -- construct from null-terminated C string
  - emString(const char* p, int len) -- construct from buffer with length
  - emString(const char* p, int len, const char* p2, int len2) -- construct by concatenation
  - emString(char c, int len=1) -- construct by filling with byte
  - ~emString()
  - static Format(const char* format, ...) -> emString -- printf-style formatting
  - static VFormat(const char* format, va_list args) -> emString
  - operator=(const emString&) -> emString&
  - operator=(const char*) -> emString&
  - operator=(char) -> emString&
  - GetCount() const -> int -- byte length (calls strlen)
  - GetLen() const -> int -- byte length (calls strlen)
  - operator const char*() const -- implicit conversion to C string
  - Get() const -> const char* -- get internal null-terminated buffer
  - operator[](int index) const -> char
  - Get(int index) const -> char
  - GetWritable() -> char* -- mutable buffer (breaks COW)
  - GetWritable(int index) -> char& -- mutable byte reference
  - SetLenGetWritable(int len) -> char* -- resize and get mutable buffer
  - Add(const emString&) -> void
  - Add(const char*) -> void
  - Add(const char*, int len) -> void
  - Add(char c, int len=1) -> void
  - operator+=(const emString&) -> emString&
  - operator+=(const char*) -> emString&
  - operator+=(char) -> emString&
  - operator+(const emString&) const -> emString
  - operator+(const char*) const -> emString
  - operator+(char) const -> emString
  - friend operator+(const char*, const emString&) -> emString
  - friend operator+(char, const emString&) -> emString
  - Insert(int index, const emString&) -> void
  - Insert(int index, const char*) -> void
  - Insert(int index, const char*, int len) -> void
  - Insert(int index, char c, int len=1) -> void
  - Replace(int index, int exLen, const emString&) -> void
  - Replace(int index, int exLen, const char*) -> void
  - Replace(int index, int exLen, const char*, int len) -> void
  - Replace(int index, int exLen, char c, int len=1) -> void
  - GetSubString(int index, int len) const -> emString
  - Extract(int index, int len) -> emString
  - Remove(int index, int len=1) -> void
  - Clear() -> void
  - IsEmpty() const -> bool
  - operator==/!=/<=/>=/</> (const emString&) const -> bool (strcmp-based)
  - operator==/!=/<=/>=/</> (const char*) const -> bool
  - friend operator==/!=/<=/>=/</> (const char*, const emString&) -> bool
  - GetDataRefCount() const -> unsigned int
  - MakeNonShared() -> void

  Implementation details (emString.cpp):
  - COW with reference-counted SharedData { RefCount, Buf[] }
  - EmptyData is a static singleton with RefCount=UINT_MAX/2
  - PrivRep handles overlapping source/target memory (memmove)
  - VFormat uses a 512-byte stack buffer, falls back to heap allocation

C++ usage in emCore (517 occurrences in headers across 67 files, 525 in .cpp across 63 files):
  emString is the most heavily used type in all of emCore. Representative usages:
  - emBorder.h (lines 52-54,68-69,414-415): Caption, Description member variables; name parameter
  - emPanel.h (line 12+): panel name, identity encoding
  - emModel.h (line 5+): model name storage
  - emFileModel.h: file path storage
  - emTextField.h (line 19+): text content storage
  - emDialog.h: title, message strings
  - emFileDialog.h (23 occurrences): file paths, directory paths, filters
  - emFileSelectionBox.h (29 occurrences): directory, selected names, filters
  - emFpPlugin.h (29 occurrences): plugin paths, names, descriptions
  - emRec.h (22 occurrences): record names, string values
  - emStd2.h (17 occurrences): utility string functions
  - emStd1.cpp (line 12+): emGetChildPath, emGetHostName, etc.
  - emStd2.cpp (46 occurrences): path manipulation, string utilities
  - emProcess.cpp (32 occurrences): command args, environment variables
  - emTextField.cpp (26 occurrences): text editing operations
  - emMiniIpc.cpp (24 occurrences): IPC message formatting
  - emInstallInfo.cpp (14 occurrences): installation path queries

Rust equivalents found:
  - emString broadly maps to String (owned) and &str (borrowed)
  - The Rust codebase uses String/&str pervasively in the same roles as emString.
  - emString() -> String::new()
  - emString(const char*) -> String::from() or .to_string()
  - Get() / operator const char*() -> .as_str() or &str borrowing
  - GetLen()/GetCount() -> .len()
  - operator[] -> .as_bytes()[i] or .chars().nth(i)
  - Add / operator+= -> String::push_str() / format!()
  - operator+ -> format!() or + operator on String
  - Insert -> String::insert_str()
  - Replace -> String::replace() or String::replace_range()
  - GetSubString -> &str slicing or String::from(&s[a..b])
  - Remove -> String::drain() or String::replace_range(range, "")
  - Clear -> String::clear()
  - IsEmpty -> String::is_empty() or str::is_empty()
  - Comparison operators -> PartialEq, PartialOrd, Ord on String/&str (lexicographic)
  - Format/VFormat -> format!() macro
  - COW/GetDataRefCount/MakeNonShared -> no equivalent (String is single-owner)
  - GetWritable/SetLenGetWritable -> direct mutable access via &mut String
  Representative String/&str usage locations:
    - src/emCore/emListBox.rs:74,133,230,232 -- String for item text, name
    - src/emCore/emBorder.rs -- &str parameters for caption, description
    - src/emCore/emColor.rs:371,380 -- &str for color parsing, String for intermediate
    - src/emCore/emInput.rs:194 -- &str for key name parsing (emStringToInputKey)
    - src/emCore/emTextField.rs -- String for text content (68 occurrences of relevant patterns)

Coverage gaps:
  - Extract(int index, int len) -> emString: no single-method equivalent found in Rust,
    but can be composed from slicing + drain/replace_range. Not found as a named method
    in the Rust codebase.
  - SetLenGetWritable: no direct equivalent. Rust String does not expose a raw buffer
    resize-then-write pattern. Callers would use String::with_capacity + push/write.
  - GetWritable(int index) -> char&: Rust strings are UTF-8 and do not support O(1)
    mutable byte access by index. Callers would use unsafe or bytes_mut().

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - The C++ emString is byte-oriented (strlen-based, no encoding assumption). Rust String
    is UTF-8. Whether any emCore code relies on non-UTF-8 byte sequences in strings is
    not verified by this audit.

